### There hasn’t been much scientific research on Type 1 diabetes and the
We’d advise that you don’t do them because they can cause lots of different
health problems, addiction and get in the way of your relationships with
A recreational drug is a drug that people take without a medical reason. Some
Different recreational drugs do different things that might cover up symptoms
of a hypo or make you feel like you’re about to have one.
Some drugs can also slow you down or give you more energy which can make your
If drugs make you lose track of time, it’s also possible you might forget to
You might also experience something called a comedown for a few days after.
Comedowns can affect your mood and make you less likely to look after yourself
If you’re going to do drugs and you feel like you can talk openly with your
healthcare team, discussing it with them would be a good way of making sure
This could just be a simple conversation about ways to manage your diabetes
while you do – this could be something like checking your blood sugar levels
If you’re going to do drugs, make sure you’re with a friend that knows about
your diabetes and knows how to recognise and help you treat a hypo.
If you want any more advice or information on drugs go to Talk to Frank.
